MASHED POTATOES

Serves 2-3; double recipe if you want more

1lb yukon gold potatoes
Milk (whole)
Butter ~1tbsp
Salt

Peel potatoes and cut into eighths. Submerge in salted water and boil for 15 minutes.
In another pan: melt butter with milk on low heat.

Drain potatoes. Add to the pan with the butter and mash using a potato masher, until they resemble
mashed potatoes. Add milk to even the consistency. Salt to taste.
